tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE model_predictions (
    prediction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    prediction_value FLOAT,
    evaluation_metric VARCHAR(50),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
    metric_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_history (
    history_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    training_loss FLOAT,
    training_time INTERVAL,
    evaluation_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    metric_name VARCHAR(50),
    metric_value FLOAT,
    evaluation_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE comparison_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model1_id INT,
    model2_id INT,
    comparison_metric VARCHAR(50),
    winning_model_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_history (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID,
    training_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    training_loss FLOAT,
    training_accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE comparison_results (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_1_id UUID,
    model_2_id UUID,
    comparison_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    winner_model_id UUID
);
